      <title>To Devs, And Those In The Know</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=OT&amp;message.id=156734#M156734</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I am looking to build a new machine.&amp;nbsp; I would like it to be powerful, reliable/stable, efficient, and cost effective.&amp;nbsp; I would like my machine to be able to perform normal computer tasks - internet surfing, word processing, etc. - and I would also&amp;nbsp;like it to be able to completely handle Everquest, from one instance bazaar mule to up to 3 boxing with full graphics and such, all without being overwhelmed if it's pushed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;My question:&amp;nbsp;Which components, configuration, etc., would you all utilize if you were to build a new machine?&amp;nbsp; In terms of manufacturers and models, what motherboard, processor, RAM and quantity, hard drive, sound and video, operating system, and all related stuff like that would you all buy in order to basically build not only a great computer, but a great gaming computer as well?&amp;nbsp; Keep in mind, I would implement a budget of say around $1500.&amp;nbsp; I understand for this much I wouldn't be able to build the best computer in the world, but I'm sure I would be able to build a really competent one.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
