      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;I assume you can build this machine.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I would focus on any of the current deals you can get from NewEgg.com or TigerDirect.com.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can start with the Mother(Main)Board+CPU combos or BareBones etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One that will do everything you want is this&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Any case for 40 to 50 dollars US.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;450 watt power supply for under 100 dollars&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;several MB+CPU combo's using the Celeron D 345 (3.06ghz) at under 100 dollars.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4 GB of Ram (you want to 3 box on the same machine with little to no impact then this is essential) figure 768mb per instance + any ram used by the OS and any running process's.&amp;nbsp; All for should be able to be had at under 400 dollars.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;NVIDIA GForce 6200 with 128MB can be had for under 50 dollars.&amp;nbsp; AGP is alive and well thank you and it really doesnt matter.&amp;nbsp; You can spend 10 to 20 times more money than this for only marginal improvements to the Graphics contribution to EQ.&amp;nbsp; And get the priviladge of throwing it all away in 4 months when the best becomes obsolete.&amp;nbsp; And you get the ability to build a museum of all the Best Vidio Cards you spent 400+ dollars on to use for 2 to 3 months.&amp;nbsp; OR you can spend under 50 dollars us for those obsoleted cards 6 months after they come out.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SATA150/300 120GB/160GB (8MB/16MB on disk cache) under 100 dollars.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;19/20 inch flat screen LCD under 250 dollars. I would focus on DVI here as well as on the Graphics Card&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;All of the above can be found on either NewEgg or TigerDirect.&amp;nbsp; And it can be 10 to 20% less than the above if you dont mind doing the rebates.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As it just so happens, I just upgraded a P3 880mhz, 512mb system when the MotherBard died.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I did not need to do the RAM, CRT, Case or Power Supply (BUT I CONSIDERED THEM :))&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I went with a Celeron D 345 (3.06GHZ) MotherBoardCombo from TigerDirect ($85US).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;NVIDIA 6200 with 128MB $45 us from TigerDirect.&lt;/p&gt;Total cost $130 US.&amp;nbsp; Total time to upgrade and get booted 1 hour.&amp;nbsp; Total time to clean install Windows XP PRO with all Windows Update upgrades, 3 hours.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When it comes down to it, should I need to junk that system, I can feel more ... comfortable juinking $130 vs junking 1500.&amp;nbsp; Actualy if I did this once a year, I would be covered for 10 years :)&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by EnigmaMaitreya on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;06-12-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;05:59 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
