nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 65&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.asp?Item=N82E16813131540" target="_blank"&gt;Motherboard&lt;/a&gt; - A very important component, but for gaming...it isn't really the piece I tweek.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 155&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.asp?Item=N82E16819103529" target="_blank"&gt;Processor&lt;/a&gt; - In most computers, the processor is actually WAITING on the rest of the computer for work to do, but since we still have a large amount of your budget left......let's go crazy.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 295&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.asp?Item=N82E16814102624" target="_blank"&gt;Graphics Card&lt;/a&gt; - This is where you want to go crazy.&amp;nbsp; This one takes two PCI slots, but who cares....do you really need to hook up that old dial-up modem?&amp;nbsp; Is onboard sound not good enough for you?&amp;nbsp; If you can find a game out that this card can't handle.....I'll buy you a new one.&amp;nbsp; Oh, and remember.....AGP IS DEAD.&amp;nbsp; PCI Express is where its at! &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 340&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.asp?Item=N82E16820134008" target="_blank"&gt;Memory&lt;/a&gt; - I recommend getting a quality brand here.&amp;nbsp; Geil is ok.&amp;nbsp; SoE loves Kingston and it is good.&amp;nbsp; Corsair..... whatever.&amp;nbsp; I would suggest buying 4 of these.&amp;nbsp; You could get 2x 2GB (the motherboard we picked out maxes at 4gigs) but that is just a huge waste of money.&amp;nbsp; 4x77&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;60+35+75+65+155+295+340+(77x4)= about 1350.&amp;nbsp; Add shipping and handling/tax and its still under 1500.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;No software though.......do you need software?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;With the extra 150 you could get a nice soundcard or a new mouse......&lt;br&gt;DO NOT BUY A WIRELESS MOUSE THAT DOESN'T HAVE A CHARGER.&amp;nbsp; You will hate it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I hope this helps.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;EDIT:&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;Also.....I dual box two characters on my computer right now.&amp;nbsp; And in the past I have done 3.&amp;nbsp; For two I had the graphics full blast on one...and completely down (except the race of that toon for mounts) on the other.&amp;nbsp; When I did 3 I turned all the graphics down completely.&amp;nbsp; I never really lagged or had problems doing it either.&amp;nbsp; Zoning 3 at once can take a while.....but it's not too bad.&amp;nbsp; I might add that the computer I use is about 1/3 as good as the one I "built" in this post.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Tip:&amp;nbsp; Only use sound on one account.&amp;nbsp; Otherwise things get a little chaotic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by NmEnforcer on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;06-10-2006&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;05:51 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
